The paper discusses the use of modeling, data analytics, and metrics to quantify the resilience of energy infrastructure and services to severe weather disruptions. This involves analyzing large-scale failures, recoveries, and impacts, as well as identifying vulnerabilities in the infrastructure and services through data analytics. These topics are relevant to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). However, given the focus on resilience and the use of data analytics, cs.CR and cs.SI are the most likely sub-categories.
